The World Bank said it has loanedUganda 13 mln dlrs through the International DevelopmentAssociation (IDA), the bank's concessionary lending affiliate.    The IDA loan will support a project that hopes to preservethe country's natural forests and meet its demand for woodproducts by rehabilitating Uganda's forestry management agency,the bank said.    It also said the project plans to increase the area andmanagement of protected forests, establish pilot wood farms andnurseries, and rehabilitate soft wood plantations. Reuter&#3;